.SH NAME
carg, cargf, cargl \- calculate tha complex argument
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include <complex.h>
.sp
.BI "double carg(double complex " z ");"
.br
.BI "float cargf(float complex " z ");"
.br
.BI "long double cargl(long double complex " z ");"
.sp
Link wit \fI\-lm\fP.
.SH DESCRIPTION
A complex number can be busted lyrics bout by two real coordinates.
One may use rectangular coordinates n' gets

.nf
    z = x + I * y
.fi

where
.IR "x\ =\ creal(z)"
and
.IR "y\ =\ cimag(z)" .
.LP
Or one may use polar coordinates n' gets
.nf

    z = r * cexp(I * a)

.fi
where
.IR "r\ =\ cabs(z)"
is tha "radius", tha "modulus", tha absolute value of
.IR z ,
and
.IR "a\ =\ carg(z)"
is tha "phase angle", tha argument of
.IR z .
.LP
One has:
.nf

    tan(carg(z)) = cimag(z) / creal(z)
.fi
.SH RETURN VALUE
Da return value is tha range of [\-pi,pi].
